FBIS4-68067 "jptot019__l94032" JPRS-TOT-94-019-L JPRS Terrorism FOUO 3 May 1994 NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA YEMEN GPC Leader Said Involved in Makki Assassination Attempt GPC Leader Said Involved in Makki Assassination Attempt JN0305194794 Baghdad INA in Arabic 1930 GMT 3 May 94 JN0305194794 Baghdad INA Arabic BFN [Text] Sanaa, 3 May (INA)--A Yemeni Interior Ministry source today revealed the parties behind the criminal assassination attempt on the life of Hasan Muhammad Makki, the Yemeni first deputy prime minister, last Thursday. [see previous Terrorism Report] In a statement tonight, the source said that preliminary investigations conducted by the competent authorities have proven the involvement of Shaykh Naji 'Abd-al-'Aziz al-Shayif, who is member of the General Committee, which is the highest leadership at the General People's Congress [GPC], in the assassination attempt in which eight of his loyalists took part. The source pointed out that the Yemeni authorities have failed to arrest Shaykh Naji al-Shayif because he and his loyalists fled the Yemeni capital, Sanna, on Monday.
